article.headline: North Texas 73, Louisiana-Lafayette 72 (OT)
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Kendrick Davis converted a three-point play with 2 seconds left in overtime, giving North Texas a 73-72 victory over Louisiana-Lafayette on Thursday night. Lafayette's David Dees caused a scare for the Mean Green (12-5, 3-3 Sun Belt) when he made a desperation shot from about 30 feet out. Officials spent several minutes reviewing the basket and determined that Dees' shot was after the buzzer. With 49 seconds remaining in regulation, Davis was fouled on a successful jumper and tied the game at 64 with the free throw. Lafayette's Elijah Millsap and Rhett Hebert each missed shots in the final seconds that would have won the game for the Ragin' Cajuns (4-13, 2-5). Davis was 8-of-13 from the field to lead the Mean Green with 22 points. Calvin Watson came off the bench to add 15 points, and Quincy Williams had 13 points and a team-high eight rebounds. Dees had 23 points for the Ragin' Cajuns, who trailed 34-33 at halftime. He went 9-of-11 from the free throw line. Millsap added 17 points and grabbed 12 rebounds. Ross Mouton had 13 points.
